{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775875137264,"sessionID":"ses_285982822ffevXkXdO724q4nnA","part":{"id":"prt_d7a681a70001OAUTcFRjfJEweZ","messageID":"msg_d7a6810d7001Gt9J5Ut5qly0Yn","sessionID":"ses_285982822ffevXkXdO724q4nnA","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_db5e82c4d0614eb8824bce4e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-032/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-032/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-032 — Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images)\n2: \n3: - **AR ID**: AR-032\n4: - **Module**: docker\n5: - **Language**: Dockerfile\n6: - **Size**: S\n7: - **Status**: ST-1 Completed (design.md)\n8: - **Stage**: ST-1\n9: \n10: ## 1. Architecture\n11: \n12: ### 1.1 Overview\n13: \n14: This design implements multi-stage Docker builds for AgentCube server components, creating 3 optimized container images from a shared Go build infrastructure. The approach reduces image size by ~60-70% compared to single-stage builds and minimizes attack surface by excluding build tools from runtime images.\n15: \n16: ### 1.2 Directory Structure\n17: \n18: ```\n19: docker/\n20: ├── base.Dockerfile           # Shared Go build environment (builder stage)\n21: ├── Dockerfile.router         # Router: builder → alpine runtime\n22: ├── Dockerfile.workload-manager  # Workload Manager: builder → alpine runtime\n23: └── Dockerfile.agentd         # Agentd + Picod: builder → alpine runtime\n24: ```\n25: \n26: ### 1.3 Image Targets\n27: \n28: | Image | Binary | Builder Base | Runtime Base | Expected Size |\n29: |-------|--------|-------------|-------------|---------------|\n30: | `agentcube-router` | router | golang:1.24-alpine | alpine:3.19 | ~25-30MB |\n31: | `agentcube-workload-manager` | workload-manager | golang:1.24-alpine | alpine:3.19 | ~30-35MB |\n32: | `agentcube-agentd` | agentd + picod | golang:1.24-alpine | alpine:3.19 | ~35-40MB |\n33: \n34: ### 1.4 Multi-Stage Build Pattern\n35: \n36: Each runtime Dockerfile uses a two-stage build pattern:\n37: \n38: ```dockerfile\n39: # Stage 1: Builder\n40: FROM golang:1.24-alpine AS builder\n41: WORKDIR /build\n42: COPY go.mod go.sum ./\n43: RUN go mod download\n44: COPY . .\n45: RUN CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux go build -o /bin/[binary] ./cmd/[binary]\n46: \n47: # Stage 2: Runtime\n48: FROM alpine:3.19 AS runtime\n49: RUN adduser -D -u 1000 agentcube\n50: USER 1000\n51: COPY --from=builder /bin/[binary] /usr/local/bin/\n52: ENTRYPOINT [\"/usr/local/bin/[binary]\"]\n53: ```\n54: \n55: ### 1.5 Component Architecture\n56: \n57: ```\n58: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n59: │                        Docker Build Process                              │\n60: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n61: │                                                                         │\n62: │  ┌──────────────┐     ┌──────────────┐     ┌──────────────┐           │\n63: │  │ go.mod/go.sum│     │ go.mod/go.sum│     │ go.mod/go.sum│           │\n64: │  └──────┬───────┘     └──────┬───────┘     └──────┬───────┘           │\n65: │         │                    │                    │                    │\n66: │         ▼                    ▼                    ▼                    │\n67: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n68: │  │                    base.Dockerfile (builder)                   │   │\n69: │  │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │   │\n70: │  │  │ FROM golang:1.24-alpine AS builder                      │   │   │\n71: │  │  │ WORKDIR /build                                          │   │   │\n72: │  │  │ COPY go.mod go.sum ./                                  │   │   │\n73: │  │  │ RUN go mod download                                    │   │   │\n74: │  │  │ COPY . .                                               │   │   │\n75: │  │  │ RUN CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux go build ./cmd/...       │   │   │\n76: │  │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │   │\n77: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n78: │         │                    │                    │                    │\n79: │         ▼                    ▼                    ▼                    │\n80: │  ┌────────────┐        ┌────────────┐        ┌────────────┐              │\n81: │  │  router    │        │workload-   │        │  agentd    │              │\n82: │  │  binary    │        │  manager   │        │  + picod   │              │\n83: │  │            │        │  binary    │        │  binaries  │              │\n84: │  └─────┬──────┘        └─────┬──────┘        └─────┬──────┘              │\n85: │        │                     │                     │                    │\n86: │        ▼                     ▼                     ▼                    │\n87: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n88: │  │                    Runtime Images (alpine:3.19)                 │   │\n89: │  │  ┌─────────────┐ ┌─────────────┐ ┌─────────────┐               │   │\n90: │  │  │agentcube-   │ │agentcube-   │ │agentcube-   │               │   │\n91: │  │  │  router    │ │workload-    │ │  agentd     │               │   │\n92: │  │  │  ~25MB     │ │  manager    │ │  ~40MB     │               │   │\n93: │  │  │             │ │  ~30MB      │ │             │               │   │\n94: │  │  └─────────────┘ └─────────────┘ └─────────────┘               │   │\n95: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n96: │                                                                         │\n97: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n98: ```\n99: \n100: ## 2. Data Structures\n101: \n102: ### 2.1 Build Arguments\n103: \n104: | Arg | Default | Required | Description |\n105: |-----|---------|----------|-------------|\n106: | `GO_VERSION` | `1.24` | No | Go toolchain version |\n107: | `BUILDER_IMAGE` | `golang:1.24-alpine` | No | Build stage base image |\n108: | `RUNTIME_IMAGE` | `alpine:3.19` | No | Runtime stage base image |\n109: | `BINARY_VERSION` | `dev` | No | Binary version info |\n110: \n111: ### 2.2 Build Environment Variables\n112: \n113: | Variable | Description |\n114: |----------|-------------|\n115: | `CGO_ENABLED` | Must be `0` for static linking |\n116: | `GOOS` | Must be `linux` for Linux containers |\n117: | `GOARCH` | Target architecture (default: amd64) |\n118: \n119: ### 2.3 Runtime Configuration\n120: \n121: | Setting | Value | Description |\n122: |---------|-------|-------------|\n123: | User | `agentcube` (UID 1000) | Non-root user for security |\n124: | Binary Location | `/usr/local/bin/` | Standard binary installation path |\n125: | Working Directory | `/home/agentcube` | User home directory |\n126: | Shell | `/bin/sh` | Alpine default shell |\n127: \n128: ### 2.4 Binary Entry Points\n129: \n130: | Binary | Command | Arguments | Environment |\n131: |--------|---------|-----------|-------------|\n132: | router | `/usr/local/bin/router` | Flags from `cmd/router/main.go` | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`, `REDIS_ADDR` |\n133: | workload-manager | `/usr/local/bin/workload-manager` | Flags from `cmd/workload-manager/main.go` | `REDIS_ADDR`, `REDIS_PASSWORD` |\n134: | agentd | `/usr/local/bin/agentd` | Flags from `cmd/agentd/main.go` | `AGENTCUBE_KUBECONFIG` |\n135: | picod | `/usr/local/bin/picod` | Flags from `cmd/picod/main.go` | `PICOD_WORKSPACE` |\n136: \n137: ## 3. API Contracts\n138: \n139: ### 3.1 Makefile Targets\n140: \n141: ```makefile\n142: # Build all images\n143: docker-build: docker-build-router docker-build-workload-manager docker-build-agentd\n144: \n145: # Build individual images\n146: docker-build-router:\n147: \tdocker build -f docker/Dockerfile.router -t agentcube-router:latest .\n148: \n149: docker-build-workload-manager:\n150: \tdocker build -f docker/Dockerfile.workload-manager -t agentcube-workload-manager:latest .\n151: \n152: docker-build-agentd:\n153: \tdocker build -f docker/Dockerfile.agentd -t agentcube-agentd:latest .\n154: \n155: # Push images to registry\n156: docker-push: docker-build\n157: \tdocker push agentcube-router:latest\n158: \tdocker push agentcube-workload-manager:latest\n159: \tdocker push agentcube-agentd:latest\n160: ```\n161: \n162: ### 3.2 Docker Build Commands\n163: \n164: ```bash\n165: # Build with custom tags\n166: docker build -f docker/Dockerfile.router -t agentcube-router:v1.0.0 .\n167: \n168: # Build with build arguments\n169: docker build -f docker/Dockerfile.router \\\n170:   --build-arg GO_VERSION=1.24 \\\n171:   --build-arg BINARY_VERSION=v1.0.0 \\\n172:   -t agentcube-router:latest .\n173: \n174: # Build with custom registry\n175: docker build -f docker/Dockerfile.router \\\n176:   -t ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube-router:latest .\n177: ```\n178: \n179: ### 3.3 Image Verification Commands\n180: \n181: ```bash\n182: # Verify binary executes\n183: docker run --rm agentcube-router version\n184: \n185: # Verify non-root user\n186: docker run --rm agentcube-router id\n187: \n188: # Check image layers\n189: docker history agentcube-router:latest\n190: \n191: # Verify no source code in image\n192: docker run --rm agentcube-router ls -la /home/agentcube\n193: \n194: # Check image size\n195: docker images agentcube-router\n196: ```\n197: \n198: ## 4. Error Handling\n199: \n200: ### 4.1 Build Errors\n201: \n202: | Error | Cause | Resolution |\n203: |-------|-------|------------|\n204: | `go: cannot find main module` | Missing go.mod in context | Ensure build context is project root |\n205: | `cannot find module` | go.sum mismatch | Run `go mod download` before build |\n206: | `cannot build binary` | Missing cmd path | Verify cmd/{binary}/main.go exists |\n207: | `stat binary: no such file` | Build failed silently | Check for compilation errors |\n208: \n209: ### 4.2 Runtime Errors\n210: \n211: | Error | Cause | Resolution |\n212: |-------|-------|------------|\n213: | `binary not found` | Incorrect COPY path | Verify binary path in Dockerfile |\n214: | `permission denied` | Binary not executable | Add chmod +x in Dockerfile |\n215: | `no such file or directory` | Missing libc | Use `CGO_ENABLED=0` |\n216: \n217: ### 4.3 Multi-Stage Build Errors\n218: \n219: | Error | Cause | Resolution |\n220: |-------|-------|------------|\n221: | `COPY --from: no such image` | Stage name typo | Verify stage names match |\n222: | `stage 'builder' not found` | Incorrect stage reference | Use `--target` flag |\n223: \n224: ### 4.4 Build Validation\n225: \n226: ```bash\n227: # Pre-build validation\n228: validate-dockerfiles:\n229: \t@echo \"Validating Dockerfiles...\"\n230: \t@docker build -f docker/base.Dockerfile --target builder --no-run .\n231: \t@echo \"Dockerfiles are valid\"\n232: \n233: # Post-build validation\n234: validate-images: docker-build\n235: \t@docker run --rm agentcube-router --help > /dev/null || (echo \"Router binary failed\" && exit 1)\n236: \t@docker run --rm agentcube-workload-manager --help > /dev/null || (echo \"Workload-manager binary failed\" && exit 1)\n237: \t@docker run --rm agentcube-agentd --help > /dev/null || (echo \"Agentd binary failed\" && exit 1)\n238: \t@docker run --rm agentcube-agentd picod --help > /dev/null || (echo \"Picod binary failed\" && exit 1)\n239: \t@echo \"All images validated\"\n240: ```\n241: \n242: ## 5. Testing Strategy\n243: \n244: ### 5.1 Unit Tests\n245: \n246: Build verification tests for each Dockerfile:\n247: \n248: ```bash\n249: # Test base Dockerfile\n250: docker build -f docker/base.Dockerfile --target builder -t agentcube-builder:test .\n251: \n252: # Test individual Dockerfiles\n253: docker build -f docker/Dockerfile.router -t agentcube-router:test .\n254: docker build -f docker/Dockerfile.workload-manager -t agentcube-workload-manager:test .\n255: docker build -f docker/Dockerfile.agentd -t agentcube-agentd:test .\n256: ```\n257: \n258: ### 5.2 Binary Execution Tests\n259: \n260: | Test | Command | Expected |\n261: |------|---------|----------|\n262: | Router version | `docker run --rm agentcube-router version` | Exit 0, output version |\n263: | Router help | `docker run --rm agentcube-router --help` | Exit 0, show help |\n264: | WM help | `docker run --rm agentcube-workload-manager --help` | Exit 0, show help |\n265: | Agentd help | `docker run --rm agentcube-agentd --help` | Exit 0, show help |\n266: | Picod help | `docker run --rm agentcube-agentd picod --help` | Exit 0, show help |\n267: \n268: ### 5.3 Security Tests\n269: \n270: | Test | Command | Expected |\n271: |------|---------|----------|\n272: | Non-root user | `docker run --rm agentcube-router id` | UID 1000, not 0 |\n273: | No source code | `docker run --rm agentcube-router ls /build` | Error/not found |\n274: | No go.mod | `docker run --rm agentcube-router cat go.mod` | Error/not found |\n275: | Minimal packages | `docker run --rm agentcube-router apk list` | Alpine base only |\n276: \n277: ### 5.4 Size Tests\n278: \n279: | Test | Command | Expected |\n280: |------|---------|----------|\n281: | Router size | `docker images agentcube-router --format \"{{.Size}}\"` | < 50MB |\n282: | Workload-manager size | `docker images agentcube-workload-manager --format \"{{.Size}}\"` | < 50MB |\n283: | Agentd size | `docker images agentcube-agentd --format \"{{.Size}}\"` | < 60MB |\n284: \n285: ### 5.5 Cache Reuse Tests\n286: \n287: ```bash\n288: # First build (cold)\n289: time docker build -f docker/Dockerfile.router -t agentcube-router:test .\n290: \n291: # Second build (warm, no changes)\n292: time docker build -f docker/Dockerfile.router -t agentcube-router:test .\n293: \n294: # Verify cache used\n295: # Expected: Second build should complete in < 30 seconds\n296: ```\n297: \n298: ### 5.6 End-to-End Tests\n299: \n300: ```bash\n301: # Integration test script\n302: #!/bin/bash\n303: set -e\n304: \n305: echo \"Building images...\"\n306: make docker-build\n307: \n308: echo \"Testing image sizes...\"\n309: for img in router workload-manager agentd; do\n310:     size=$(docker images agentcube-$img --format \"{{.Size}}\" | sed 's/MB//')\n311:     if (( $(echo \"$size > 60\" | bc -l) )); then\n312:         echo \"FAIL: agentcube-$img exceeds size limit: $size MB\"\n313:         exit 1\n314:     fi\n315:     echo \"PASS: agentcube-$img size: $size MB\"\n316: done\n317: \n318: echo \"Testing binary execution...\"\n319: docker run --rm agentcube-router version\n320: docker run --rm agentcube-workload-manager --help\n321: docker run --rm agentcube-agentd --help\n322: docker run --rm agentcube-agentd picod --help\n323: \n324: echo \"Testing non-root execution...\"\n325: docker run --rm agentcube-router id | grep \"uid=1000\"\n326: \n327: echo \"All tests passed!\"\n328: ```\n329: \n330: ---\n331: \n332: ## References\n333: \n334: - Docker multi-stage builds: https://docs.docker.com/build/buildkit/\n335: - Alpine Linux container best practices: https://wiki.alpinelinux.org/wiki/Docker\n336: - Go static builds: https://github.com/golang/go/wiki/GoReleaser\n337: - Delta spec: `changes/AR-032/delta-spec.md`\n338: - Proposal: `changes/AR-032/proposal.md`\n339: - Helm chart (AR-030): `manifests/agentcube/values.yaml`\n\n(End of file - total 339 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-032 — Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images)\n\n- **AR ID**: AR-032\n- **Module**: docker\n- **Language**: Dockerfile\n- **Size**: S\n- **Status**: ST-1 Completed (design.md)\n- **Stage**: ST-1\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Overview\n\nThis design implements multi-stage Docker builds for AgentCube server components, creating 3 optimized container images from a shared Go build infrastructure. The approach reduces image size by ~60-70% compared to single-stage builds and minimizes attack surface by excluding build tools from runtime images.\n\n### 1.2 Directory Structure\n\n```\ndocker/\n├── base.Dockerfile           # Shared Go build environment (builder stage)","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-032/design.md","time":{"start":1775875137245,"end":1775875137261}}}}
